**Key findings from the analysis:**

Strongest, biologically-expected prognostic signals (all multivariable-significant): ECOG (-1.17 mo/pt), albumin (+0.46/g/dL), weight loss (-0.075/pct), CEA (-0.005/ng/mL), LDH, CRP, right-sided primary (-0.29), KRAS (-0.36), BRAF V600E (-0.36), stage IV (-1.35).

Refuted treatmentĂ—biomarker predictive relationships: cetuximabĂ—KRAS/NRAS/BRAF, pembrolizumabĂ—MSI-high, encorafenibĂ—BRAF-V600E, trastuzumab/tucatinibĂ—HER2-amp â€” none of the interaction terms reached significance and within-subgroup effects were near zero.

Unexpected: regorafenib showed a robust +0.94 mo PFS benefit (p â‰ˆ 0) in both unadjusted and full multivariable models, not modified by line, ECOG, or biomarker status. Older age was univariately associated with *longer* PFS. No race/ethnicity, insurance, rural, or education disparities were detectable. No SNP survived Bonferroni correction.
